  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How do I get over a crush on my guy best friend?",
  "response": "Navigating a crush on a close friend can be challenging but manageable. Here are some steps you can take to help get over your feelings:\n\n1. **Acknowledge Your Feelings**: Recognize that having a crush is normal. Accepting your feelings can help you process them.\n\n2. **Reflect on the Friendship**: Consider what you value about your friendship. This can help you focus on the positive aspects of your relationship and may lessen romantic feelings.\n\n3. **Set Boundaries**: If your feelings are impacting the friendship, it might be helpful to establish some emotional distance. This could involve spending less time together or engaging in different activities.\n\n4. **Focus on Yourself**: Invest time in hobbies, interests, and friendships outside of this person. This can help redirect your thoughts and energies.\n\n5. **Consider Talking About It**: If you feel comfortable and believe it won\u2019t harm your friendship, you might discuss your feelings with your friend. Being open can sometimes relieve emotional pressure.\n\n6. **Limit Comparisons**: Avoid comparing him to potential romantic interests. This can help you see him as just a friend rather than someone to idealize.\n\n7. **Explore New Relationships**: Allow yourself the opportunity to meet new people and potentially develop new crushes. This can shift your focus away from your current feelings.\n\n8. **Practice Mindfulness**: Engage in mindfulness or relaxation techniques. They can help you navigate your emotions and reduce anxiety surrounding your crush.\n\n9. **Seek Support**: Talk to a trusted friend or counselor about your feelings. They can provide perspective and help you process your emotions.\n\n10. **Give It Time**: Feelings often shift over time. Allow yourself the space to move through your feelings without rushing the process.\n\nRemember, it's okay to feel the way you do, and with time and self-care, it's likely that you'll be able to move past your crush.",
